The most common bug to avoid in this function is an incorrect base case or recursive call that fails to consider all possible subsets of the input list. 

```python
def subset_sum(xs, target):
    def helper(xs, target, index):
        if target == 0:
            return True
        if index == len(xs) or target < 0:
            return False
        return helper(xs, target - xs[index], index + 1) or helper(xs, target, index + 1)
    return helper(xs, target, 0)
```
